abstract: Joint List coalition, alliance of Arab parties, wins 13 seats in Israel's next Parliament, making it the third-largest bloc.
lead_paragraph: The Arab cohort, which calls itself the Joint List, received 13 seats in Israel’s next Parliament. But as the euphoria in Arab towns fades, it remains far from clear what influence it will actually have.

headline.main: Voters in Nazareth Cheer Gains by Arab Alliance
